"Conducted seminaries at Utica and Canandaigua New York","body":"After his Hartford Asylum tenure, Samuel and his wife Abigail Goodrich conducted 'large seminaries' at Utica and Canandaigua New York. While in Utica in 1832 Abigail began publishing The Mother's Magazine, the early American periodical of maternal Christian instruction she would edit for nearly two decades."}],"education":[{"institution":"Yale College","institution_id":"INST002","graduation_year":1803,"degree":"B.A.","honors":"Phi Beta Kappa; A.M."}],"slug":"samuel-whittlesey-1775"},"I00434":{"id":"I00434","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Abigail","maiden_name":"Goodrich","married_names":["Whittlesey"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Abigail Goodrich Whittlesey","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1778349799/abilgailgwhittlesey-resized_miuoy8.png"},"birth":{"year":1788,"month":11,"day":29,"city":"Ridgefield","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1858,"month":7,"day":16},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_research_notes":"Family of Goodrich (Ridgefield Conn.). Educated at Berlin Conn."},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD0102","date_year":1808,"date_month":11,"date_day":10,"location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","children_ids":["HD3790","HD3791","HD3792","HD3793","HD3794","HD3795","HD3796"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["literature"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"literature","header":"Edited Mother's Magazine for nearly two decades","body":"Abigail began publishing 'The Mother's Magazine' in 1832 while in Utica New York, editing it until about 1850. She subsequently revived it under the title 'Magazine for Mothers,' running one of the earliest American periodicals devoted to maternal Christian instruction."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB005","page":"Entry 360 (under Samuel Whittlesey, his wife)"}],"documents":[],"slug":"abigail-goodrich-1788"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM044","name":"Arlington National Cemetery","city":"Arlington","county":"Arlington","state":"Virginia","country":"United States","lat":38.8769,"lng":-77.0733,"visitable":true,"notes":"National military cemetery. Burial place of Dr. John Minor (HD2760), WW1 veteran. Absorbed duplicate CEM475 Stage 6Y-691 per compiler ruling; the nation’s preeminent military cemetery — every attached ID verified retained in the merge audit.","sources":[],"hooker_connections":["HD0338","HD1206","HD1691","HD1759","HD2561","HD2563","HD2760","HD3015","HD3127","HD3850","HD3858","HD3916","HD4045","I00479","I00484","I00517","TD0150","X00385","X00569","X00855","X02053","X02071","X02091","I00696","HD5258","HD5858","I01512","HD6282","X03197","HD6078","X03325","X03326","I00970","HD4817","HD4709","HD4710","I01072","HD4702"],"person_ids":["HD3850","HD3858","I00479","I00484"],"gps":{"latitude":38.8783,"longitude":-77.0687}},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}